Pressed 1 a bajillion times and it was like &quot;no i hate you im not going to work!&quot;<br>
clicking with mouse didnt work either for a few times, but by then i LoH'd a corpse /whine.<br>
<br>
and note.. it sucks being KoS in PoG and falling asleep to wake up next day in PoG still~  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujcasetn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jcasetn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 99<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/30/02 6:27:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15087.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LOH Failing</span><hr size=1> The hotkey for loh has failed me before.  I had one that went:<br>
<br>
/target me<br>
/doability 4<br>
<br>
What happened was that because of lag (I suspect - it was in a nagafen fight) I didn't get targeted and ended up wasting my loh on nagafen.  <br>
<br>
So I created another one that looked like this for nagafen take 2:<br>
<br>
/target me<br>
/target me<br>
/target me<br>
/doability 4<br>
<br>
I figured that would ensure I was targeted.  So I hit my hotkey, got killed by nagafen and repoped at my bind spot in east freeport.  Then my loh went off and I was healed for zero hitpoints.  <br>
<br>
The whole idea of the hotkey is to reduce the time it takes to kick off the loh.  In situations where I know I'll be using it for myself I bring up the ability menu at about 50percent health and position the mouse over the button.  Then I rest my finger on the TAB key.  That hasn't failed me yet.  I really wish I could hotkey this reliably though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukattootacit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kattoo Tacit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/30/02 6:59:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15087.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> LoH Targetting</span><hr size=1> It may be a good idea to try to get LoH to NEVER go off on a mob. Much like casting BMB.... BMB will cast on your group with a mob targeted. LoH would be much more 'user friendly' (&lt;---  Attention getting for those VI programmers.) if it would heal the casting Paladin rather than the mob on target.  How many times has anyone wanted to use LoH on a mob? ....   never   I think it would be a great addition to the game and would be relatively easy for them to fix.<br>
<br>
Baron Kattoo Tacit<br>
Crusader of Mithaniel Marr<br>
Imperial Guards<br>
Druzzil Ro <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukattootacit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kattoo Tacit</A> at: 3/30/02 7:00:06 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dalantia>Dalantia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/31/02 8:45:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15087.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LoH Targetting</span><hr size=1> My LoH macro is this.<br>
<br>
/say It's not over yet!<br>
(One of three things)<br>
/chat 1 Healtouching %t!<br>
/say Healtouching %t!<br>
: brushes %T with the Purest Love of Erollisi Marr.<br>
/doability (LoH)<br>
<br>
